net.vivialconnect.model.connector

Class Connector

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.vivialconnect.model.VivialConnectResource
      • net.vivialconnect.model.connector.Connector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, ConnectorWithCallbacks, ConnectorWithPhoneNumbers

    public class Connector
extends VivialConnectResource
implements ConnectorWithCallbacks, ConnectorWithPhoneNumbers
    Connector is used for managing connectors and their components. Connectors act as configurable gateways through which messages can be sent, providing services like callback configuration and FROM number pooling.

    Connectors enable to:

    • Send messages from a pool of numbers
    • Change FROM numbers without editing your code
    • Manage callbacks for multiple numbers

      • update

        public Connector update()
                 throws ForbiddenAccessException,
                        BadRequestException,
                        UnauthorizedAccessException,
                        ServerErrorException,
                        ApiRequestException
        Updates this connector.

        The only property available for update is name. Therefore, be sure to call setName(String) before calling this method if you want to update it. The id property should also be set.

        Keep in mind that this method does not update neither the callbacks nor the phone numbers. To do that, you have to call updateCallbacks() and/or updateAssociatedPhoneNumbers(), which use separate resource endpoints of their own.

        If the connector you're trying to update does not exist, a VivialConnectException holding a 404 response code will be thrown.

        Returns:
        this instance of Connector with the updated name
        Throws:
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs

      • addCallback

        public Connector addCallback(Callback callback)
        Use this method to add callbacks which can later be saved to the server using createCallbacks() or updateCallbacks(). This method call can be chained in a builder-like fashion, like so: 
         
 class CallbackCreator {

  public void addAllCallbacks(Connector connector) {
    Callback c1 = new Callback();
    c1.setMessageType("text");
    c1.setEventType("incoming");

    Callback c2 = new Callback();
    c2.setMessageType("text");
    c2.setEventType("status");

    connector.addCallback(c1).addCallback(c2).createCallbacks();
  }
 }
        Parameters:
        callback - the callback to be added
        Returns:
        this instance of Connector
        See Also:
        Callback, setCallbacks(java.util.List), createCallbacks(), updateCallbacks()

      • addPhoneNumber

        public Connector addPhoneNumber(PhoneNumber phoneNumber)
        Use this method to add phone numbers which can later be saved to the server using associatePhoneNumbers() or updateAssociatedPhoneNumbers(). This method call can be chained in a builder-like fashion, like so: 
         
 class PhoneNumberCreator {

  public void addAllPhoneNumbers(Connector connector) {
    PhoneNumber p1 = new PhoneNumber();
    p1.setPhoneNumberId(29);
    p1.setPhoneNumber("+13022136859");

    PhoneNumber p2 = new PhoneNumber();
    p2.setPhoneNumberId(30);
    p2.setPhoneNumber("+13022136850");

    connector.addPhoneNumber(c1).addPhoneNumber(c2).createCallbacks();
  }
 }
        Parameters:
        phoneNumber - the phone number to be added
        Returns:
        this instance of Connector
        See Also:
        PhoneNumber, addPhoneNumber(int, String), setPhoneNumbers(List), associatePhoneNumbers(), updateAssociatedPhoneNumbers()

        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs
        See Also:
